### Using Text-Based Locators and Attribute Assertions in Java

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/writing-tests-java.md

Shows how to create a locator using text content and perform assertions on element attributes. The locator finds an element containing "Get Started" text, verifies its href attribute value, and then performs a click action. This demonstrates Playwright's locator creation, attribute validation, and element interaction capabilities.

```java
import static com.microsoft.playwright.assertions.PlaywrightAssertions.assertThat;

Locator getStarted = page.locator("text=Get Started");

assertThat(getStarted).hasAttribute("href", "/docs/intro");
getStarted.click();
```

