### LocatorAssertions.toHaveScreenshot (with name)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-locatorassertions.md

This assertion waits until two consecutive locator screenshots yield the same result, then compares the last screenshot with an expected named snapshot. This assertion is designed for visual regression testing and only works with Playwright test runner.

```APIDOC
## ASSERTION LocatorAssertions.toHaveScreenshot (with name)

### Description
This function will wait until two consecutive locator screenshots yield the same result, and then compare the last screenshot with the expectation. Note that screenshot assertions only work with Playwright test runner.

### Method
ASYNC METHOD

### Endpoint
LocatorAssertions.toHaveScreenshot

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
- **None**

#### Query Parameters
- **timeout** (number) - Optional - Maximum time in milliseconds for the assertion to pass.
- **animations** (string) - Optional - Whether to disable animations. Default is `disabled`.
- **caret** (string) - Optional - Whether to hide the caret during screenshot. Possible values: `'hide'`, `'initial'`.
- **mask** (Array<Locator>) - Optional - An array of locators that should be masked in the screenshot.
- **maskColor** (string) - Optional - Color to mask elements with, e.g., `'#FF00FF'`.
- **stylePath** (string) - Optional - Path to a CSS file to inject into the page before taking a screenshot.
- **omitBackground** (boolean) - Optional - Hides default white background and allows capturing screenshots with transparency. Default is `false`.
- **scale** (string) - Optional - Scale of the screenshot. Possible values: `'css'` (default), `'device'`.
- **maxDiffPixels** (number) - Optional - An acceptable amount of pixels that are different between the actual and expected screenshot. Defaults to 0.
- **maxDiffPixelRatio** (number) - Optional - An acceptable ratio of pixels that are different between the actual and expected screenshot. Defaults to 0.
- **threshold** (number) - Optional - A threshold between 0 and 1. Visual difference less than or equal to this threshold is considered a match. Defaults to 0.

#### Request Body
- **name** (string|Array<string>) - Required - Snapshot name(s) to compare against.

### Request Example
```js
const locator = page.getByRole('button');
await expect(locator).toHaveScreenshot('image.png');
```

### Response
#### Success Response (Assertion Passes)
The assertion passes if the locator's screenshot matches the expected snapshot within the specified tolerance.

#### Response Example
No explicit return value; the assertion either passes silently or throws an error if it fails.
```

