### Locator Assertions: Visibility

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-locatorassertions.md

Assertions to check if a locator is visible within the DOM.

```APIDOC
## TO BE VISIBLE

### Description
Ensures that a locator points to an attached and visible DOM node.

### Method
`toBeVisible()` or `isVisible()`

### Endpoint
N/A (Assertion method)

### Usage
```javascript
// A specific element is visible.
await expect(page.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();

// At least one item in the list is visible.
await expect(page.getByTestId('todo-item').first()).toBeVisible();
```

```java
// A specific element is visible.
assertThat(page.getByText("Welcome")).isVisible();

// At least one item in the list is visible.
assertThat(page.getByTestId("todo-item").first()).isVisible();
```

```python async
# A specific element is visible.
await expect(page.get_by_text("Welcome")).to_be_visible()

# At least one item in the list is visible.
await expect(page.get_by_test_id("todo-item").first).to_be_visible()
```

```python sync
# A specific element is visible.
expect(page.get_by_text("Welcome")).to_be_visible()

# At least one item in the list is visible.
expect(page.get_by_test_id("todo-item").first).to_be_visible()
